						<summary>

						<p>Lintel of the northern entrance into the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 17th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It records the obeisance of Jūṭuri Bōḍamarāju, the <hi rend="italic">karaṇam</hi> of Turimiḷḷadinne.</p>						

						</summary>
